results.name: Number of superior prime-power divisors of n.
comment: We define a divisor d|n to be superior if d >= n/d. Superior divisors are counted by A038548 and listed by A161908.
example: The superior prime-power divisors (columns) of selected n:
xref: Positions of zeros after the first are A051283.
The version for prime instead of prime-power divisors is A341591.
The version for squarefree instead of prime-power divisors is A341592.
The version for odd instead of prime-power divisors is A341675.
The strictly inferior version is A341677.
A001221 counts prime divisors, with sum A001414.
A033677 selects the smallest superior divisor.
A056924 counts strictly superior (or strictly inferior) divisors.
